message.content: This question requires understanding of the role of a producer in an ecosystem. A producer, such as a plant, is able to make its own sustenance through the process of photosynthesis. Option (B) is incorrect because producers do not produce their own air, they release oxygen as a byproduct of photosynthesis. Option (C) is incorrect because producers do not create their own shelter.
